diglerdirk, you must work for BRG.  BRG have demonstrated that they can't cook their burgers to customer's requested temperature,  I've been to BRG at least 10 times and for example Rays Hellburger at least 15 times. I always request medium rare for my burgers. BRG regularly overcooks their burger to *beyond medium* [about 8 outta 10 times]. Rays on the other hand advocates medium-rare as their "recommended" temperature & I've found regularly cooks their burger properly to temp [about 8 outta 10 times]. Just like a steakhouse, I expect burgers to be cooked to customer temp [especially if you're only a burger joint, I'd expect you to train your folks to consistently cook burgers to various temps]. Can't do that? You can't be considered the best. That belongs to Rays, Palena, or maybe Central. Look, it's a decent burger, and I recommend their pre-formatted burgers to their made-to-order stuff. But not cooking to requested temperature is a huge knock imo.
